==English==
===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} '''[[εξωσκελετός]]''' (''exoskeletos''), from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[έξω]]''' (''exo'') "out, outside, without, but, except" + '''[[σκελετός]]''' "[[skeleton]]".
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''exoskeleton'''

# {{anatomy}} A [[hard]] [[outer]] [[structure]] that provides both [[structure]] and [[protection]] to [[creature]]s such as [[insect]]s and [[Crustacea]].

